<ul>
  <li>Downloaded and Installed <a href="http://hortonworks.com/downloads/#sandbox">Hortonworks Sandbox</a></li>
  <li>
    <p>Before entering hello HDP labs, we <strong>highly recommend</strong> you go through <a href="http://hortonworks.com/hadoop-tutorial/learning-the-ropes-of-the-hortonworks-sandbox/">Learning the Ropes of the Hortonworks Sandbox</a> to become familiar with the Sandbox in a VM and the Ambari Interface.</p>
  </li>
  <li>Data Set Used: <a href="https://app.box.com/HadoopCrashCourseData"><strong>Geolocation.zip</strong></a></li>
  <li><strong><em>Optional</em></strong>: Hortonworks ODBC driver installed and configured – see the tutorial on installing the ODBC driver for Windows or OS X. Refer to
    <ul>
      <li><a href="http://hortonworks.com/hadoop-tutorial/how-to-install-and-configure-the-hortonworks-odbc-driver-on-windows-7/">Installing and Configuring the Hortonworks ODBC driver on Windows 7</a></li>
      <li><a href="http://hortonworks.com/hadoop-tutorial/how-to-install-and-configure-the-hortonworks-odbc-driver-on-mac-os-x/">Installing and Configuring the Hortonworks ODBC driver on Mac OS X</a></li>
